## Notes From This Week

The three members who went for direct customer interviews came back with something we didn't fully expect — almost everyone reacted more strongly to the GPS-triggered food ordering feature than to the parking marketplace. Most people had already tried pre-ordering food on Zomato and given up because of timing issues. The parking problem was known and accepted; the food timing problem felt more solvable and exciting to them.

One insight that stood out: a respondent mentioned they skip meals during work drives because parking near restaurants is unpredictable. That connection — parking uncertainty directly causing skipped meals — wasn't something we had in our original problem framing. We're adding it to the product statement.

Shashank's Google Form is ready to go out — once we get 20+ responses it'll give us quantitative backing for the qualitative stories from the direct interviews.

Overall a strong first week. Foundation is set.
